# Frontend patterns

- One view per file in `js/views/` — export `mount()` and `unmount()`
- Data via `js/services/dataService.js`; HTTP via `js/api/client.js` (`X-EMS-Route` for logical paths)
- Auth via `js/services/authService.js` → `auth/exchange` when live
- Router: `js/router.js`; event context via `selectedEventId` in `js/state/appState.js`
- Keep `USE_MOCK_API` path until backend endpoint exists for that feature
- Render dynamic/remote data with `js/utils/dom.js` `el({ text })` or `textContent` — never `innerHTML` (XSS). `htmlToElement()` is for trusted static markup only. See `frontend-security.mdc`.

## When changing features

- Update `docs/ui-routes.md` if routes or views change
- Align with `docs/product-flows.md` or flag stakeholder review
- Minimal diffs — no drive-by refactors
- Do not edit `project-blueprint.md` unless the user asks

Before finishing: event-centric nav, no bypass auth, brand tokens used.
